title.narrative: Partnership with the EU to improve competitiveness of the Palestinian private sector and create jobs

description.narrative: This activity (Partnership with the EU to improve competitiveness of the Palestinian private sector and create jobs) is a component of Palestinian Market Development Programme to Strengthen the Private Sector in the Occupied Palestinian Territories (OPTs) reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Procurement of Services' and a budget of £13,958,647. This component benefits Occupied Palestinian Territories (OPT), and works in the following sector(s): Business Policy and Administration, Small and medium-sized enterprises (SME) development. , with the following implementing partners: Crown Agents Bank, DAI Europe. The start date is 21-10-2013 and the end date is 30-06-2019.
